WEBVTT

00:05.339 --> 00:06.340
Y'all gonna just stand around,

00:06.374 --> 00:08.609
or you wanna ask me
some questions?

00:08.642 --> 00:10.311
<i>Dad got fired from his
job at the White House.</i>

00:10.344 --> 00:11.579
We can move anywhere.

00:11.612 --> 00:13.247
<i>Daddy did not get fired.</i>

00:13.280 --> 00:14.648
Mitchell will be the
one holding the bag, trust me.

00:14.682 --> 00:16.050
<i>Probably be happy
to go to prison</i>

00:16.083 --> 00:17.451
<i>to get away from Martha.</i>

00:17.485 --> 00:19.520
<i>Conspiracy to commit burglary</i>

00:19.553 --> 00:20.755
<i>and wiretapping.</i>

00:20.788 --> 00:22.757
I sentence you
to the maximum penalty

00:22.790 --> 00:24.525
allowable under federal law.

00:24.558 --> 00:26.127
<i>We'll reconvene
in two months' time</i>

00:26.160 --> 00:27.528
<i>to formalizing sentencing.</i>

00:27.561 --> 00:29.397
<i>You ever threaten
to squeal again,</i>

00:29.430 --> 00:31.532
it'll be the last time
you ever squeal.

00:31.565 --> 00:33.367
Pat Gray is feeding me
their reports, okay?

00:33.401 --> 00:34.735
You satisfied?

00:34.769 --> 00:36.237
<i>Oh, director
of the FBI. Very impressive.</i>

00:36.270 --> 00:37.438
It's only a matter of time

00:37.471 --> 00:38.572
<i>before they figure out
what's going on.</i>

00:38.606 --> 00:40.107
Maybe it's the routine
that scares me.

00:40.141 --> 00:41.509
<i>I just want you to know</i>

00:41.542 --> 00:43.077
<i>I can't imagine the rest
of my life without it.</i>

00:43.110 --> 00:44.812
My own boy, Jay, is over there

00:45.045 --> 00:46.614
<i>fighting for his life
as we speak.</i>

00:46.647 --> 00:48.816
- Who is it for you?
- My little brother.

00:49.049 --> 00:51.218
I'm a doer. I don't just
sit around and do nothing.

00:51.252 --> 00:52.720
<i>And if you don't do
your own talking,</i>

00:52.753 --> 00:55.256
<i>someone is gonna do it for you
in this town.</i>

00:55.289 --> 00:56.290
<i>Should the Nixon administration</i>

00:56.323 --> 00:57.725
be afraid of you,
Mrs. Mitchell?

00:57.758 --> 00:59.293
Well, I think you know
the answer to that.

00:59.326 --> 01:00.594
Attagirl, Martha.

01:12.640 --> 01:14.642
Good afternoon.

01:14.675 --> 01:16.510
Uh, the president would like
to assure the public

01:16.544 --> 01:18.446
that when it comes
to illicit profit

01:18.479 --> 01:22.450
from land deals in California,
uh, he has nothing to hide,

01:22.483 --> 01:25.286
uh, despite what leftist
Democrats might allege.

01:26.420 --> 01:27.655
<i>On the contrary,
the president</i>

01:27.688 --> 01:29.690
<i>has paid his full
and normal tax load,</i>

01:29.723 --> 01:31.859
<i>just like any citizen.</i>

01:32.092 --> 01:34.128
Therefore, an examination
of his personal taxes

01:34.161 --> 01:36.163
at this point
feels like a political ploy

01:36.197 --> 01:38.365
and is simply not necessary.

01:38.399 --> 01:40.167
Any further update
on the subject

01:40.201 --> 01:42.203
will come through
official channels, uh,

01:42.236 --> 01:45.172
before you hear it in the
secretarial pool at <i>The Post.</i>

01:46.440 --> 01:47.441
<i>And with that,
I'd like to open it up</i>

01:47.475 --> 01:48.742
to any questions.

01:48.776 --> 01:50.311
- Mr. Ziegler.
- <i>Over here.</i>

01:50.344 --> 01:51.445
Helen.

01:51.479 --> 01:53.714
Yes, I was wondering
if the White House

01:53.747 --> 01:56.584
has any comments
on the accusations

01:56.617 --> 01:58.886
currently being levied
against the president--

01:59.119 --> 02:01.222
Yeah, now uh, before you go
any further, Helen.

02:01.255 --> 02:02.556
Uh, I have been made aware

02:02.590 --> 02:04.658
that there is a certain
citizen individual

02:04.692 --> 02:06.260
who has gotten herself
some attention,

02:06.293 --> 02:07.561
uh, in the press as of late--

02:07.595 --> 02:08.696
Martha Mitchell.

02:08.729 --> 02:11.665
Well, I'm not naming
any names, Helen.

02:11.699 --> 02:13.534
<i>Um, but I would
just like to say</i>

02:13.567 --> 02:15.569
<i>that we all have
a certain nature,</i>

02:15.603 --> 02:18.138
something to which
we must adhere.

02:18.172 --> 02:20.508
And the nature of this
particular individual

02:20.541 --> 02:23.410
has been rather bellicose
and unreliable.

02:26.847 --> 02:28.549
Please welcome a woman
who's fast becoming

02:28.582 --> 02:30.551
the biggest thorn
in Richard Nixon's side

02:30.584 --> 02:32.553
since Pat shoved him
into the rose garden...

02:33.654 --> 02:35.489
...the captivating, controversial,

02:35.523 --> 02:37.358
undeniable Martha Mitchell.

02:38.626 --> 02:40.561
Mike, you make me sound
like a best seller.

02:40.594 --> 02:42.630
Now, Martha,
you are the first person

02:42.663 --> 02:44.431
that I'm aware of
to publicly accuse

02:44.465 --> 02:47.268
the president of responsibility
for the Watergate break-in.

02:47.301 --> 02:49.236
Pretty sure
I won't be the last.

02:49.270 --> 02:52.540
But Mrs. Mitchell's making
some very grave accusations

02:52.573 --> 02:53.908
against the president.

02:53.941 --> 02:55.376
I would be remiss to point out

02:55.409 --> 02:57.511
that they are accusations
that no one else has made.

02:57.545 --> 02:59.580
<i>President Nixon
has been re-elected</i>

02:59.613 --> 03:00.581
<i>by a landslide.</i>

03:03.617 --> 03:05.719
<i>♪ Sitting
Cross-legged on the floor ♪</i>

03:05.753 --> 03:07.187
Will you marry me?

03:09.924 --> 03:12.326
<i>♪ Twenty-five
Or six to four... ♪</i>

03:12.359 --> 03:14.361
<i>I, Richard Nixon,
do solemnly swear</i>

03:14.395 --> 03:17.398
<i>I will faithfully
execute the office</i>

03:17.431 --> 03:19.600
<i>of president
of the United States.</i>

03:19.633 --> 03:20.868
You also accused the president

03:20.901 --> 03:23.470
of ordering your alleged
imprisonment in California.

03:23.504 --> 03:25.739
Yes, I do, and I-I also believe

03:25.773 --> 03:27.341
that the president
is attempting

03:27.374 --> 03:30.311
to leave my husband holding
the bag for his dirty tricks,

03:30.344 --> 03:31.679
and I won't let that happen.

03:31.712 --> 03:33.314
You always speak
your mind on our show, Martha.

03:33.347 --> 03:34.782
- We really appreciate that.
- I do. I speak my mind.

03:34.815 --> 03:36.550
I am a Southern woman.
We speak our minds.

03:36.584 --> 03:38.485
We talk. I never stop talking.

03:38.519 --> 03:39.820
I bet your husband
just loves that.

03:39.853 --> 03:41.555
He takes it in stride.

03:43.257 --> 03:47.761
<i>♪ Wanting just
To stay awake... ♪</i>

03:47.795 --> 03:49.697
What?

03:49.730 --> 03:51.231
They're admirers.

03:53.367 --> 03:54.602
Jimmy, it's been so long,

03:54.635 --> 03:56.503
I was beginning to think
we weren't friends anymore.

03:56.537 --> 03:58.272
<i>♪ Should I try
To do some more... ♪</i>

03:58.305 --> 04:00.407
What you hearing at <i>The Tribune</i>
these days, anyway?

04:00.441 --> 04:02.309
I don't think the woman's
in her right mind.

04:02.343 --> 04:04.411
She might
call herself a Republican,

04:04.445 --> 04:06.246
but she's not one of us.

04:06.280 --> 04:07.281
She's a truth teller.

04:07.314 --> 04:08.282
Well, look at what they did

04:08.315 --> 04:09.516
to poor Dorothy Hunt?

04:09.550 --> 04:11.318
She was on that horrible plane
that crashed,

04:11.352 --> 04:13.587
and then they found
$10,000 cash on her.

04:13.621 --> 04:15.623
Seeing as how this person
cannot be stopped

04:15.656 --> 04:17.591
or reasoned with in any way,

04:17.625 --> 04:19.326
uh, the White House
harbors the fervent hope

04:19.360 --> 04:21.895
that she can avail herself
of familial comfort

04:21.929 --> 04:22.997
and professional help.

04:42.950 --> 04:45.019
Oh!

04:45.052 --> 04:46.820
<i>What do you say
about the rumors</i>

04:46.854 --> 04:48.789
out of the White House that
you've struggled with alcohol?

04:48.822 --> 04:51.392
I say a rumor is just
a lie without a home.

04:52.326 --> 04:54.061
She's a lush
and a pill popper too.

04:54.294 --> 04:56.296
She's got problems
emotionally and whatnot,

04:56.330 --> 04:57.564
but, um, who doesn't?

04:59.800 --> 05:01.902
<i>They were the ones
that stonewalled</i>

05:01.935 --> 05:04.638
Wright Patman's committee
in the House last October.

05:04.672 --> 05:05.739
Well, then I can be
your source,

05:05.773 --> 05:06.974
'cause I'm telling you
it's factual.

05:07.007 --> 05:08.375
Oh, you know
what I forgot to ask you?

05:08.409 --> 05:10.077
Did you get those Hummels
I sent after the wedding?

05:10.310 --> 05:11.679
And you stated elsewhere
that your goal

05:11.712 --> 05:13.047
is to take down Nixon.

05:13.080 --> 05:15.416
But the president's approval
numbers just keep climbing.

05:15.449 --> 05:16.650
If the American people

05:16.684 --> 05:18.652
knew half of what I do
about their government,

05:18.686 --> 05:20.521
they wouldn't have much
to approve of.

05:20.554 --> 05:21.989
So Mrs. Mitchell's behavior

05:22.022 --> 05:24.725
isn't getting to the first lady
or the president,

05:24.758 --> 05:26.326
as has been reported?

05:26.360 --> 05:27.695
Do you hear yourself
when you ask these questions?

05:27.728 --> 05:28.962
I mean, for criminy's sake,
come on.

05:28.996 --> 05:30.464
Let me ask
the obvious question.

05:30.497 --> 05:31.999
What is obvious?

05:32.032 --> 05:33.333
Are you crazy?

05:33.367 --> 05:34.501
Yeah.

05:37.604 --> 05:38.639
Frickin' loudmouth.

05:38.672 --> 05:39.673
Freedom-loving.

05:39.707 --> 05:40.974
Limousine liberal.

05:41.008 --> 05:42.009
Groovy liberated.

05:42.042 --> 05:43.577
Commie bitch.

05:52.986 --> 05:54.388
<i>All rise.</i>

05:55.756 --> 05:57.491
<i>This court is now in session</i>

05:57.524 --> 06:00.594
<i>with the Honorable
Judge John Sirica presiding.</i>

06:01.762 --> 06:02.963
You may be seated.

06:07.801 --> 06:10.137
Gentlemen, I called you in
today for a formal sentencing.

06:10.370 --> 06:13.841
But first,
I'd like to say a few words.

06:13.874 --> 06:16.110
<i>When I was a younger man,</i>

06:16.143 --> 06:19.446
<i>Jack Dempsey
was my sparring partner.</i>

06:20.881 --> 06:22.049
<i>I don't say that to boast,</i>

06:22.082 --> 06:24.718
<i>and I certainly
don't say it to imply</i>

06:24.752 --> 06:27.154
that I wasn't getting pummeled
every Tuesday at the Y.

06:29.556 --> 06:32.426
But I know what it means
to have heart.

06:32.459 --> 06:34.595
And frankly, the group of you
have shown a lot of heart,

06:34.628 --> 06:37.664
<i>taking all the licks you have
in this courtroom.</i>

06:37.698 --> 06:41.068
<i>And I believe
it's to be commended.</i>

06:41.101 --> 06:43.137
<i>But a fighter also has to know</i>

06:43.170 --> 06:45.405
<i>when it's time
to throw in the towel.</i>

06:46.607 --> 06:49.877
Which brings me
to a very interesting letter

06:49.910 --> 06:51.145
I received this morning...

06:54.148 --> 06:55.883
...from Mr. McCord.

06:55.916 --> 06:58.452
<i>"Certain questions
have been posed to me</i>

06:58.485 --> 07:00.888
<i>from Your Honor through
the probation officer"--</i>

07:00.921 --> 07:02.122
You rat fuck!

07:02.156 --> 07:04.958
I'll fucking--
I'll fucking kill you!

07:04.992 --> 07:05.959
<i>Order!</i>

07:05.993 --> 07:07.528
I will fucking kill you!

07:07.561 --> 07:09.029
- <i>Remove him!</i>
- You fuck!

07:09.062 --> 07:10.964
<i>I'll fucking kill you!</i>

07:10.998 --> 07:13.100
You fuck!
I should've fucking killed you

07:13.133 --> 07:14.601
when I had the chance!

07:14.635 --> 07:16.770
- <i>Get him out of here!</i>
- You fuck!

07:53.607 --> 07:54.608
Come in.

07:57.845 --> 08:01.148
The partners brought these over
for you to sign.

08:01.181 --> 08:03.550
How are you settling in?

08:03.584 --> 08:04.952
Oh, you know.

08:04.985 --> 08:06.186
I know.

08:07.621 --> 08:10.724
Looking like
you got a little sun.

08:10.757 --> 08:12.125
Oh, stop.

08:12.960 --> 08:14.828
Any calls from the White House?

08:18.065 --> 08:20.167
They're probably just...

08:20.200 --> 08:22.135
busy.

08:22.169 --> 08:25.973
I ran two of Dick's campaigns,
the ones he won.

08:26.940 --> 08:29.543
<i>The least you'd think
I could expect is to get</i>

08:29.576 --> 08:32.880
a goddamn fucking call back.

08:34.648 --> 08:38.652
Oh, I never saw that one.

08:38.685 --> 08:40.787
<i>Look at those two young men.</i>

08:40.821 --> 08:42.289
Not my best angle.

08:42.522 --> 08:44.791
Oh, stop. You look handsome.

08:45.959 --> 08:48.862
You know, I always wondered.

08:50.097 --> 08:52.566
Do he and Pat ever...

08:53.800 --> 08:56.169
Oh.

08:56.203 --> 08:58.071
Not since Trish was born.

09:04.211 --> 09:05.245
Too bad.

09:06.546 --> 09:09.783
And, uh, Mr. Mitchell,
if you ever need anything,

09:09.816 --> 09:11.285
uh, I'm right outside
your door.

09:11.318 --> 09:12.719
You know that, right?

09:12.753 --> 09:15.022
Of course. Thank you, Diana.

09:41.915 --> 09:44.284
God damn it.

09:44.318 --> 09:45.686
<i>I'm sorry</i>

09:45.719 --> 09:46.954
<i>to bother you again,
Mr. Mitchell,</i>

09:46.987 --> 09:49.056
<i>but I-I think you should
turn on the news.</i>

09:52.626 --> 09:54.194
In what reads like a wish list

09:54.227 --> 09:56.997
for the prosecution,
James McCord's letter alleges

09:57.030 --> 10:00.100
a massive campaign
of sabotage and obstruction

10:00.133 --> 10:02.069
on the part
of the Nixon administration.

10:02.102 --> 10:04.805
Reports from Capitol Hill
cite Mr. McCord's letter

10:04.838 --> 10:07.074
as a reason to open
a Senate committee

10:07.107 --> 10:09.009
dedicated
to the Watergate matter.

10:09.042 --> 10:10.644
If that happens, both present

10:10.677 --> 10:12.879
and former members
of the administration

10:12.913 --> 10:15.015
may become targets
of the investigation.

10:15.048 --> 10:16.650
<i>The news will come as a shock</i>

10:16.683 --> 10:18.352
<i>to the newly
re-elected president,</i>

10:18.385 --> 10:20.620
<i>who might have considered
the burgeoning scandal</i>

10:20.654 --> 10:22.189
<i>safely behind him.</i>

10:26.159 --> 10:28.195
<i>"Mr. McCord
has joined lone voices</i>

10:28.228 --> 10:30.764
"in the wilderness
such as Martha Mitchell

10:30.797 --> 10:33.300
"in publicly implicating
the president's closest aides

10:33.333 --> 10:34.801
in the Watergate break-in."

10:34.835 --> 10:36.203
Well, at least now
they will see

10:36.236 --> 10:38.405
I was right about
the whole rotten lot of 'em.

10:38.638 --> 10:39.806
Are you sure
you don't want any?

10:39.840 --> 10:40.974
Yes, thank you.

10:41.008 --> 10:42.776
Mm.

10:42.809 --> 10:45.679
Boy, they've really
got 'em lined up now.

10:45.712 --> 10:47.381
Bunch of bowling pins.

10:48.749 --> 10:51.151
Martha, can we focus
on the book?

10:51.184 --> 10:53.253
I-I really wanna get
some work done today.

10:54.087 --> 10:55.822
Oh. Of course.

10:55.856 --> 10:57.891
You have my undivided attention.

10:59.059 --> 11:01.028
So the Pine Bluffs
records office

11:01.061 --> 11:03.330
didn't have a death certificate
on file for your father--

11:03.363 --> 11:05.298
Oh, Maria! Ooh!

11:06.233 --> 11:09.302
This is my good friend Maria
from back in the New York days.

11:09.336 --> 11:11.738
Maria, this is
Winzola McLendon.

11:11.772 --> 11:15.175
She is my biographer
and a first-rate journalist.

11:15.208 --> 11:16.777
Right up there
with Helen Thomas.

11:17.978 --> 11:19.846
A biography?

11:19.880 --> 11:23.784
Martha, you are too much
for this town, I swear.

11:23.817 --> 11:25.786
Oh, guess who I ran into
at the A&P.

11:25.819 --> 11:27.020
- Who?
- <i>Jay.</i>

11:28.755 --> 11:30.257
Jay, your son?

11:30.290 --> 11:32.225
You said he was
still in Vietnam.

11:32.259 --> 11:34.795
Oh, no, he's been
stateside for a while now.

11:34.828 --> 11:36.763
Living with all those Jews
down in Baltimore.

11:36.797 --> 11:39.733
<i>He's such a kind boy.
Won the Silver Star, you know.</i>

11:39.766 --> 11:41.368
Purple Heart.
Now, did he mention to you

11:41.401 --> 11:43.336
that he has moved in with
that little girlfriend of his?

11:43.370 --> 11:45.072
I darn near hit the roof.

11:46.039 --> 11:48.208
Can I interview him?
For the book.

11:48.241 --> 11:50.811
But you have me,
the greatest source of all.

11:52.712 --> 11:56.183
Yes, it just might be
interesting is all.

11:57.284 --> 11:59.052
Well, of course,
if that's what you want to do,

11:59.086 --> 12:00.887
but I will give you
a piece of advice.

12:00.921 --> 12:02.122
<i>If that little girlfriend
of his</i>

12:02.155 --> 12:04.758
invites you over for dinner,
take an entrée.

12:04.791 --> 12:06.259
She's a vegetarian.

12:08.462 --> 12:10.764
Although there are reports
that the convicted

12:10.797 --> 12:12.933
Watergate conspirators
might be first

12:12.966 --> 12:15.235
to testify
at the formal hearings,

12:15.268 --> 12:17.337
which begin a week
from Thursday,

12:17.370 --> 12:20.140
Ervin and Baker would only say
that the witness list

12:20.173 --> 12:21.942
will be out later this week.

12:21.975 --> 12:23.844
<i>And the first set
of hearings will last...</i>

12:23.877 --> 12:24.978
<i>Hey there!</i>

12:25.011 --> 12:27.214
How's married life
treating you, champ?

12:27.247 --> 12:28.849
Uh, it's only been
a week,

12:28.882 --> 12:31.118
but so far, so good.

12:31.151 --> 12:32.486
Yeah, Mo is a-a little peeved

12:32.519 --> 12:34.454
we had to stick around D.C.,
and, uh--

12:34.488 --> 12:37.491
Oh, I'm so sorry you had
to cancel your honeymoon.

12:37.524 --> 12:40.827
Now this damn McCord letter's
gotten everybody in a fright.

12:40.861 --> 12:42.095
Yeah, no, it's, uh--
it's all right.

12:42.129 --> 12:43.797
You know, we hadn't
actually left yet,

12:43.830 --> 12:46.433
so it was just a matter
of unpacking.

12:46.466 --> 12:48.068
<i>Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.</i>

12:48.101 --> 12:51.171
Well, still, the president,
he feels awful about it.

12:51.204 --> 12:53.440
He and the first lady
would like to gift you

12:53.473 --> 12:55.008
a little getaway weekend.

12:55.041 --> 12:56.977
<i>Something to tide you over
until you and the missus</i>

12:57.010 --> 12:59.079
can spring
for the real honeymoon.

13:02.149 --> 13:03.884
- You gotta be shitting me.
- No.

13:03.917 --> 13:05.785
<i>President never shits anyone
about Camp David.</i>

13:05.819 --> 13:08.121
<i>Here are the keys.</i>

13:08.155 --> 13:10.857
Directions, list of amenities
should be included.

13:10.891 --> 13:11.892
This is unbelievable.

13:11.925 --> 13:15.896
I-I--thank you so, so much. I--

13:15.929 --> 13:16.997
Oh, my God, Mo's gonna flip.

13:17.030 --> 13:19.132
I--this--
I don't know what to say.

13:19.166 --> 13:20.467
- You earned it. No.
- Oh.

13:20.500 --> 13:22.169
And look, it'll be good
to have a little time away

13:22.202 --> 13:24.404
from the city to write that
investigative report, right?

13:26.006 --> 13:27.874
I'm sor--um...

13:27.908 --> 13:31.111
sorry, i-investigative report?

13:31.912 --> 13:33.246
Oh, yeah. Did nobody tell you?

13:34.381 --> 13:36.349
Oh, huh. Oh, okay.

13:36.383 --> 13:38.585
No, it's just something, uh,
Dick wants typed up.

13:38.818 --> 13:41.121
