that go with this necklace,
and I just cannot--

29:22.394 --> 29:23.963
Now I'm late.

29:23.996 --> 29:24.964
<i>...here
on the par-three golf course</i>

29:24.997 --> 29:27.032
<i>on Monday night...</i>

29:27.066 --> 29:28.300
You have been moping for weeks

29:28.334 --> 29:32.071
while I have been out
defending our reputation.

29:32.104 --> 29:33.072
Oh.

29:33.105 --> 29:34.373
From where I sit,

29:34.406 --> 29:37.209
looks a bit more self-serving
than that.

29:37.243 --> 29:39.145
Self-serving?

29:39.178 --> 29:41.280
Look at these freaks.

29:41.313 --> 29:43.849
Free Martha Mitchell!

29:43.883 --> 29:47.887
You're practically a teen idol,
just what you always wanted.

29:48.787 --> 29:51.223
<i>That'll goose book sales.</i>

29:51.257 --> 29:52.491
We're looking
at boarding schools.

29:52.525 --> 29:54.293
Be sure to clear your schedule.

29:55.261 --> 29:56.862
Diana'll take care of that.

29:56.896 --> 29:58.297
She's very attentive.

30:04.170 --> 30:06.539
Don't, uh, let Marty
stay up too late.

30:07.873 --> 30:10.442
And there's pot roast in
the kitchen if you get hungry.

30:11.877 --> 30:13.579
I won't.

30:18.384 --> 30:20.219
What the hell, Bob?

30:20.252 --> 30:21.487
Come on, you--

30:21.520 --> 30:24.423
No, you said I didn't have
to write that report.

30:24.456 --> 30:25.591
Well, the president's
plastering it

30:25.824 --> 30:26.859
all over the news.

30:26.892 --> 30:28.294
That's-that's my name
out there.

30:28.327 --> 30:29.929
I could go to jail for this.

30:29.962 --> 30:32.531
Listen. I am on your side.

30:32.565 --> 30:35.467
But Dick just isn't
gonna budge on this.

30:35.501 --> 30:37.870
If you nut up
and do the right thing,

30:37.903 --> 30:40.406
then it'll just be
a lot easier for everyone.

30:40.439 --> 30:42.074
Is-is that a threat?

30:42.107 --> 30:43.409
Of course not, buddy.

30:43.442 --> 30:45.911
I just want to help you
get out of your own way.

30:45.945 --> 30:47.479
I hope you're having fun
up there.

30:48.480 --> 30:51.116
No, Bob. Bob? Bob?

30:52.551 --> 30:55.054
What song is sung at a
dress-up party on Fire Island?

30:58.357 --> 31:00.559
Fuck! Fuck! Fuck! Fuck!

31:07.266 --> 31:11.370
I feel like
something's going on.

31:20.012 --> 31:21.113
Whoo-ooh.

31:34.026 --> 31:36.895
Somebody was hungry.

32:02.221 --> 32:04.523
<i>I just--I feel strong
when I'm with you.</i>

32:04.556 --> 32:06.358
<i>Like I can do anything.</i>

32:06.392 --> 32:08.127
<i>Oh, John.</i>

32:08.160 --> 32:09.361
<i>When we're in the office together,</i>

32:09.395 --> 32:11.263
<i>I can barely stand it.</i>

32:11.297 --> 32:14.233
<i>I want you inside me so badly.</i>

32:14.266 --> 32:17.303
<i>Mm. Soon.</i>

32:17.336 --> 32:19.204
<i>We'll book a room
at the Roosevelt</i>

32:19.238 --> 32:20.706
<i>and sneak off.</i>

32:40.693 --> 32:42.628
You really think
this is gonna work,

32:42.661 --> 32:44.697
just sitting here like this?

32:44.730 --> 32:46.732
Oh, yeah.

32:46.965 --> 32:48.233
Big-time.

32:48.267 --> 32:50.569
Once we had
this potential witness

32:50.602 --> 32:51.970
in a white-collar case.

32:52.004 --> 32:53.972
Criminal mastermind
like this guy here.

32:54.006 --> 32:55.741
<i>We did everything
to get him to talk,</i>

32:55.974 --> 32:57.009
<i>but nothing worked.</i>

32:57.042 --> 32:58.510
<i>Then my partner
gets this idea,</i>

32:58.544 --> 32:59.611
stake out his house
for the weekend

32:59.645 --> 33:01.647
just for the fuck of it.

33:01.680 --> 33:04.550
I'm telling you,
within seven hours,

33:04.583 --> 33:08.187
this asshole comes out
to the car and says he'll talk.

33:08.220 --> 33:10.389
- Wow.
- Yeah.

33:10.422 --> 33:12.324
It's one thing to feel like
a criminal when you're alone.

33:12.358 --> 33:13.525
It's another thing to feel it

33:13.559 --> 33:15.427
when you're with your wife,
your children.

33:15.461 --> 33:19.765
It feels invasive somehow, unbearable.

33:19.998 --> 33:22.334
He'll be singing
to the special prosecutor

33:22.368 --> 33:24.236
by tomorrow morning.

33:24.269 --> 33:26.438
<i>Deputy campaign director.</i>

33:26.472 --> 33:27.773
Guy shouldn't be
deputy director

33:28.006 --> 33:30.642
of a fuckin' White Castle.

33:30.676 --> 33:33.078
It--this is some charmed
gringo shit right here.

33:33.112 --> 33:36.348
- That's what that is.
- What do you mean, gringo shit?

33:36.382 --> 33:38.384
You saw when new assignments
went up last week, right?

33:38.417 --> 33:39.585
Yeah.

33:39.618 --> 33:40.719
All the Hispanic guys
got shit jobs, right?

33:40.753 --> 33:42.087
Well...

33:42.121 --> 33:43.288
- Well?
- Yeah.

33:43.322 --> 33:46.425
- Translation. Transcription.
- Okay.

33:46.458 --> 33:48.060
You know what they used
to call guys like me

33:48.093 --> 33:49.428
- when I was at the Academy?
- What?

33:49.461 --> 33:50.462
The Taco Squad.

33:50.496 --> 33:51.730
Don't laugh.

33:51.764 --> 33:53.732
That's cafeteria shit-talk.

33:53.766 --> 33:55.067
It's not a big thing.

33:56.301 --> 33:58.370
So you're telling me

33:58.404 --> 34:01.573
it wouldn't get under your skin
if you were part of the--

34:01.607 --> 34:04.243
I don't know,
the-the-the Dago Division?

34:07.279 --> 34:09.348
Look, I'm just sayin',

34:09.381 --> 34:13.352
we're all jockeying for a spot
at the trough, right?

34:13.385 --> 34:15.687
Even Sergeant Dickhead
over here.

34:15.721 --> 34:18.190
You have to drink something.

34:18.223 --> 34:20.626
- It's a hot one.
- Yeah.

34:23.295 --> 34:24.396
Okay.

34:35.541 --> 34:37.676
<i>Why didn't you tell me
about this, John?</i>

34:37.709 --> 34:39.111
I don't know.

34:40.846 --> 34:41.847
I'm such an idiot.

34:42.080 --> 34:44.650
I just--I thought if I--

34:44.683 --> 34:46.084
if I kept it all a secret,

34:46.118 --> 34:49.087
then eventually,
it would just...

34:49.121 --> 34:50.155
go away.

34:50.189 --> 34:51.790
That's the logic
of a five-year-old.

34:51.824 --> 34:53.492
I'm-I'm-I'm your wife.

34:53.525 --> 34:54.827
<i>That's not really
how this works.</i>

34:54.860 --> 34:57.229
I know. I know.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

34:57.863 --> 34:59.498
Okay, so this
investigative report

34:59.531 --> 35:00.799
that Haldeman
wants you to write--

35:00.833 --> 35:04.203
<i>I told you
the report is a sham.</i>

35:05.304 --> 35:08.841
If I write it,
I am the first official

35:08.874 --> 35:11.276
with knowledge of the cover-up
to lie about it publicly.

35:11.310 --> 35:12.344
That is what they want.

35:12.377 --> 35:13.745
They wanna pin it on me

35:13.779 --> 35:16.748
so that they can squash
any more investigations.

35:16.782 --> 35:18.650
What happens
if you refuse to do that?

35:20.352 --> 35:23.288
Th-they'll draw and quarter me
in the press.

35:23.322 --> 35:24.456
They'll destroy me.

35:24.490 --> 35:26.525
You don't know
what kind of tools

35:26.558 --> 35:28.393
they have
at their disposal, Mo.

35:28.427 --> 35:29.795
I should know, I've used them.

35:29.828 --> 35:32.865
Oh, my God.
Stop talking.

35:32.898 --> 35:34.233
I know I let you down. I-I'm--

35:34.266 --> 35:35.434
I-I didn't mean
to keep things from you.

35:35.467 --> 35:37.469
I just--it all got out of hand.

35:37.503 --> 35:38.537
Okay.

35:40.305 --> 35:42.808
I'm only gonna say this
one time, okay?

35:42.841 --> 35:46.378
You cannot ever do this
to me again, ever.

35:47.513 --> 35:48.647
I know.

35:50.282 --> 35:51.383
Okay.

35:52.451 --> 35:54.419
Now, you obviously
can't write that report,

35:54.453 --> 35:56.421
and we cannot let them
drag you through the press.

35:56.455 --> 35:57.823
So what's the third option?

35:57.856 --> 36:00.492
I-I can't just walk

36:00.526 --> 36:02.427
into the special prosecutor's
office.

36:02.461 --> 36:03.629
Why not?

36:03.662 --> 36:05.898
Because I'm-I'm at the center
of this thing.

36:05.931 --> 36:07.366
I'm the bad guy.

36:07.399 --> 36:09.601
Well, what if you're the guy
who saw an injustice

36:09.635 --> 36:11.370
and decided to do something
about it?

36:12.404 --> 36:14.273
Wh-what do you mean?

36:14.306 --> 36:17.376
I'm saying--okay, if you
come out against these people,

36:17.409 --> 36:19.411
these criminals,

36:19.444 --> 36:21.580
you no longer have
a legal problem, right?

36:21.613 --> 36:24.583
You have, what,
a-a-a PR problem.

36:24.616 --> 36:25.584
And you know what?

36:25.617 --> 36:26.818
I-I've spent my entire life

36:26.852 --> 36:29.588
creating versions of myself
to please people

36:29.621 --> 36:30.789
to get what I want,

36:30.822 --> 36:33.258
and what I want is for you
not to go to jail.

36:33.292 --> 36:36.228
So we just...

36:36.261 --> 36:38.397
teach you how to do that.

36:38.430 --> 36:39.898
We're gonna have you
tell the truth

36:39.932 --> 36:42.634
in a way
that America likes you.

36:42.668 --> 36:44.636
Create a version of you that
people can see themselves in.

36:44.670 --> 36:46.672
I think that's
how we win this, John.

36:46.705 --> 36:48.340
That's how we get free.

36:49.975 --> 36:51.643
You just have to trust me.

36:51.677 --> 36:52.978
Oh.

36:55.781 --> 36:58.550
I mean, do you trust me?

36:58.584 --> 36:59.585
Yes.

37:03.622 --> 37:07.225
I love you... so much.

37:11.663 --> 37:13.298
Thank you both so much
for meeting me.

37:13.332 --> 37:15.567
Oh, thank you.

37:15.601 --> 37:16.969
Um, I would offer you some,

37:17.002 --> 37:19.605
but I-I hear
that you're a vegetarian.

37:19.638 --> 37:22.240
Martha told you that?

37:22.274 --> 37:23.575
Fantastic.

37:25.811 --> 37:27.946
So, um, listen, Jay,

37:27.980 --> 37:29.648
I was surprised
when your mom mentioned

37:29.681 --> 37:31.617
that you were back
from overseas.

37:33.819 --> 37:35.754
Well, actually, I've been back
a few years now.

37:35.787 --> 37:37.389
My mother sometimes
likes to tell people

37:37.422 --> 37:38.957
from the press
I'm still fighting.

37:38.991 --> 37:41.426
You know,
exaggerate for effect.

37:41.460 --> 37:42.828
Drunks tend to do that.

37:44.796 --> 37:47.966
Um, and I have here
that your father, Clyde,

37:48.000 --> 37:50.302
divorced your mother in 1957.

37:50.335 --> 37:51.503
<i>Yeah, that's right.</i>

37:51.536 --> 37:54.306
I-I guess she met Mr. Mitchell
the year before,

37:54.339 --> 37:56.675
and, um, I was nine,

37:56.708 --> 37:58.510
so I-I don't really know
much about that.

37:58.543 --> 37:59.978
Okay.

38:00.012 --> 38:03.715
And, um, what can you tell me
about growing up with your mom?

38:03.749 --> 38:06.685
Um, anything will help,
um, you know,

38:06.718 --> 38:08.520
memories, anecdotes,
that sort of thing.

38:08.553 --> 38:12.791
Yeah, yeah. Uh, oof. Well...

38:12.824 --> 38:15.994
Look, there is a reason why
Martha never talks about Jay.

38:16.028 --> 38:17.362
- Well--
- It's because

38:17.396 --> 38:18.697
she left him behind
with everything else

38:18.730 --> 38:21.033
from her past
that she'd prefer to forget.

38:21.066 --> 38:23.735
- I-I'm sorry?
- Sharon--

38:23.769 --> 38:25.871
She is a selfish,
troubled woman

38:25.904 --> 38:28.740
who happened to raise
a sensitive and loving son.

38:28.774 --> 38:30.308
But I don't credit that
to her mothering

38:30.342 --> 38:31.777
any more than I credit
a hurricane

38:31.810 --> 38:33.812
for the next sunny day.

38:33.845 --> 38:35.480
Understand?

38:36.648 --> 38:38.717
Yeah.

38:38.750 --> 38:40.352
Right.

38:40.385 --> 38:43.488
Now, if you will excuse me,
I have to use the ladies' room.

38:53.065 --> 38:54.366
Sorry about that.

38:54.399 --> 38:56.668
She's just
a little protective of me.

38:56.702 --> 38:57.836
That's okay.

38:57.869 --> 38:59.738
Strong women
tend to be that way.

39:02.641 --> 39:04.643
I brought something
that I wanted to give you.

39:08.480 --> 39:09.781
It's just some things
of my mother's

39:09.815 --> 39:12.084
that I've collected
over the years.

39:12.117 --> 39:14.519
Old photos.

39:14.553 --> 39:16.088
Stuff she left behind.

39:16.121 --> 39:18.657
Uh, maybe it might help
with your book.

39:19.658 --> 39:20.625
Of course.

39:20.659 --> 39:22.627
Thank-thank you so much.
That's--

39:22.661 --> 39:24.096
So how's she doing, anyway?

39:25.464 --> 39:26.898
She's fine.

39:26.932 --> 39:30.068
Yeah, she's playing
a pretty dangerous game

39:30.102 --> 39:31.570
with the press right now,

39:31.603 --> 39:36.007
antagonizing the White House
like that, but, uh...

39:36.041 --> 39:38.777
she's tough, your mom.

39:38.810 --> 39:41.613
You know, she has a way of, um,

39:41.646 --> 39:43.014
working against herself.

39:43.048 --> 39:44.816
Yeah, that sounds like her.

39:44.850 --> 39:46.384
There are days when I think

39:46.418 --> 39:49.154
I should just move on
and cover something else,

39:49.387 --> 39:53.425
but she calls me up
and wins me over, so...

39:53.458 --> 39:57.395
Look, I know my mom
is a lot to handle...

39:59.030 --> 40:02.467
...but don't give up on her.

40:06.671 --> 40:07.973
Thank you.

40:13.979 --> 40:16.815
Martha, if we don't leave now,
we're gonna be late.

40:19.117 --> 40:20.819
Great,
it's a boarding school tour,

40:20.852 --> 40:22.454
not La Scala. Come on.

40:22.487 --> 40:23.822
Well, I have to wear it somewhere.

40:23.855 --> 40:25.824
Otherwise, it's a waste,
and you never take me anywhere.

40:25.857 --> 40:27.125
Zolton's been
waiting an hour down there.

40:27.159 --> 40:29.060
You're awfully grumpy. Up late?

40:29.094 --> 40:30.729
Not now.

40:30.762 --> 40:32.164
I'll take a number
like everybody else.

40:32.197 --> 40:33.532
What are we up to now?

40:33.565 --> 40:34.733
Don't listen
to your mother.

40:34.766 --> 40:36.568
She's full of stories.

40:36.601 --> 40:38.103
And gin.

40:39.471 --> 40:41.506
I'd have to be drunk
to put up with you.

40:49.714 --> 40:51.016
These are our social grounds,

40:51.049 --> 40:53.685
a place to relax
with new friends.

40:55.487 --> 40:58.089
- Eyes forward.
- Stop it.

40:58.123 --> 40:59.825
I'd say
they're all too young for you,

40:59.858 --> 41:01.526
but you never listen
to your wife.

41:01.560 --> 41:03.228
We are not gonna do this here.

41:04.529 --> 41:05.564
Oh, I think that one

41:05.597 --> 41:07.065
might have
her learner's permit.

41:09.868 --> 41:12.504
<i>Over this way,
you'll see the sports courts.</i>

41:12.537 --> 41:15.507
We believe a healthy body
promotes a healthy mind.

41:15.540 --> 41:18.109
Mm, maybe I should
take a lover too,

41:18.143 --> 41:19.711
take the pressure off.

41:19.744 --> 41:21.479
You're the one that
keeps creating the pressure,

41:21.513 --> 41:23.849
the one on television
every second of the day.

41:23.882 --> 41:25.016
Shh.

41:25.050 --> 41:26.084
<i>Well, I wouldn't
have to go on TV</i>

41:26.117 --> 41:27.719
if you had the guts
to speak out.

41:27.752 --> 41:30.722
Oh, God. Not this again.
I can't take it anymore.

41:30.755 --> 41:32.924
Hey.
Could you guys keep it down?

41:32.958 --> 41:34.626
Keep yourself down, buddy.

41:34.659 --> 41:36.228
- Excuse me?
- Come on, Martha.

41:36.261 --> 41:37.529
There are children here.

41:37.562 --> 41:39.064
Tell them to mind
their own damn business.

41:39.097 --> 41:41.733
Hey, pal,
might wanna handle your wife.

41:41.766 --> 41:43.602
- The hell you say to me?
- Dad.

41:43.635 --> 41:44.803
Maybe this is the reason

41:44.836 --> 41:46.605
the president canned you, asshole.

41:46.638 --> 41:47.873
How dare you speak
to my husband like that?

41:47.906 --> 41:48.874
If I can direct your attention

41:48.907 --> 41:49.941
to the field hockey area?

41:49.975 --> 41:51.009
What are you gonna do, lady?

41:51.042 --> 41:52.244
You gonna go on TV
and make a sucker

41:52.277 --> 41:53.612
out of me
like you did to your husband?

41:53.645 --> 41:56.081
Stop it. Stop it.

41:57.015 --> 41:59.084
You smug little prick.

41:59.117 --> 42:00.652
<i>Dad.</i>

42:00.685 --> 42:01.887
Oh!

42:08.059 --> 42:09.227
- Jackass.
- Jerk.

42:14.165 --> 42:15.834
You all right, darling?

42:15.867 --> 42:17.869
Mitchell. Oh!

42:17.903 --> 42:19.004
Dad?

42:19.037 --> 42:20.005
<i>Somebody get a doctor, please.</i>

42:20.038 --> 42:21.873
Somebody get a doctor.

42:21.907 --> 42:24.309
<i>What's wrong?
What's happening?</i>

42:24.542 --> 42:27.045
Just catch your breath.
Just catch your breath.

42:27.078 --> 42:29.047
<i>Daddy, what's wrong?</i>

42:29.080 --> 42:31.116
Daddy, are you okay?

42:47.666 --> 42:48.733
Fuck.

42:48.767 --> 42:49.968
They not teach you
to use a waste bin

42:50.001 --> 42:51.069
at the Academy? My word.

42:51.102 --> 42:54.205
Uh, Mrs.-Mrs. Magruder.

42:54.239 --> 42:56.641
Hello. May, uh--

42:56.675 --> 42:58.810
can we--can we help you?

42:58.843 --> 43:01.746
My husband,
he suffers from the nocturia.

43:02.314 --> 43:03.748
Um...

43:03.782 --> 43:05.083
- what?
- The what?

43:05.116 --> 43:06.284
Nocturia.

43:06.318 --> 43:08.320
It's a medical term
for an overactive bladder

43:08.353 --> 43:09.854
brought on by anxiety.

43:09.888 --> 43:12.991
So when he's nervous,
he has to pee, and so he pees.

43:13.024 --> 43:15.160
<i>But right away, he immediately
gets this burning sensation</i>

43:15.193 --> 43:16.895
like he has to go again.

43:16.928 --> 43:19.731
It's just a trick
his mind is playing on him.

43:19.764 --> 43:21.633
Uh...

43:21.666 --> 43:23.802
I'm-I'm sorry, Mrs. Magruder--

43:23.835 --> 43:25.203
Call me Gail.

43:26.604 --> 43:28.773
Uh, sure, Gail.

43:28.807 --> 43:31.042
<i>Why are you telling us this?</i>

43:31.076 --> 43:32.210
Mmm.

43:33.244 --> 43:36.915
Because ever since
the two of you amateurs

43:36.948 --> 43:39.217
have been sitting
outside of my house,

43:39.250 --> 43:42.754
Jeb has been inside going
back and forth to the restroom

43:42.787 --> 43:44.689
as if it's an Olympic sport.

43:44.723 --> 43:47.258
The poor dummy is convinced
you boys are gonna haul him off

43:47.292 --> 43:49.861
to some secret prison
in Bolivia or something.

43:49.894 --> 43:52.197
He can't stop peeing.
It's driving me crazy.

43:52.230 --> 43:54.833
Well, we sympathize
with you, Gail.

43:54.866 --> 43:58.203
But if Jeb didn't want anyone
looking over his shoulder,

43:58.236 --> 44:00.038
maybe he shouldn't have
gotten himself involved

44:00.071 --> 44:02.974
in a criminal conspiracy.

44:03.008 --> 44:04.843
You're not listening to me.

44:04.876 --> 44:08.179
My husband is not
an intelligent man.

44:08.213 --> 44:09.681
Yeah.

44:09.714 --> 44:10.982
<i>But he knows
how to do the right thing.</i>

44:11.016 --> 44:14.386
A few days ago, I was
this close to convincing him

