than to be

48:37.048 --> 48:38.316
with you and your brothers.

48:38.349 --> 48:42.186
But some things are more
important than what we want.

48:43.221 --> 48:46.924
Now, place the phone down
so you can hear my voice.

48:50.495 --> 48:52.030
Back straight.

48:54.632 --> 48:56.601
When I was a boy,

48:56.634 --> 48:57.969
I was very ill.

48:59.370 --> 49:03.107
My only friend was my nanny,
Frau Teresa.

49:04.075 --> 49:08.212
One night, as I lie awake,
dying of pneumonia,

49:08.246 --> 49:11.382
she told me the story
of another sickly little boy,

49:11.416 --> 49:15.486
a boy who, from the power
of his own will,

49:15.520 --> 49:17.155
overcame death

49:17.188 --> 49:20.258
and became the leader
of her fatherland,

49:20.291 --> 49:22.193
a mighty and terrible Fuehrer

49:22.226 --> 49:24.662
whose name would echo
through time.

49:25.663 --> 49:27.332
Frau Teresa made me realize

49:27.365 --> 49:29.967
that I, too, could overcome
my own frailty,

49:30.001 --> 49:32.637
that I, too,
could choose to be strong.

49:34.639 --> 49:36.674
So hear me now.

49:36.708 --> 49:41.245
The three of you individually
are very small...

49:41.279 --> 49:44.582
but combined,
you're equal to one adult man.

49:44.615 --> 49:45.683
And with me gone,

49:45.717 --> 49:47.185
you're gonna need
to start acting like it.

49:48.586 --> 49:52.090
James, no more fear
of the dark or monkeys.

49:53.491 --> 49:57.328
Tommy, no more crying
when the phone rings.

49:59.130 --> 50:01.366
Is...

50:01.399 --> 50:04.268
prison scary, Father?

50:04.302 --> 50:06.204
Terrifying.

50:07.004 --> 50:10.375
